          "author": {
            "login": "ConcaveTrillion"
          },
          "body": "Filed from the pd-book-tools deep code/security review.\n\nReport: `docs/research/2026-05-22-deep-code-security-review.md`\nFinding: #25\n\nMoved from mistakenly filed meta issue: ConcaveTrillion/ocr-container-meta#318\n\nEvidence:\n\n- `pyproject.toml:100`\n- `pyproject.toml:102`\n- `.gitlab-ci.yml:55`\n\nCuPy modules are omitted from coverage, and GPU CI is allowed to fail.\n\nImpact:\n\n- CUDA code can regress without affecting quality gates.\n\nRemediation:\n\n- Keep CPU coverage separate if needed, but add GPU coverage with its own threshold.\n\n---\nThis issue was filed from a read-only review. Confirm behavior with a focused failing test before implementation where practical.",
          "closedAt": "2026-05-25T02:48:49Z",
          "comments": {
            "nodes": [
              {
                "author": {
                  "login": "ConcaveTrillion"
                },
                "body": "Fixed in commit aed3962 (Batch C agent). The cupy_processing omit was removed from [tool.coverage.run] in pyproject.toml. GPU modules now count toward the 87% threshold. Post-fix coverage: 90.0%.",
