          "author_association": "OWNER",
          "body": "Filed from the pd-book-tools deep code/security review.\n\n    Report: `pd-book-tools/docs/research/2026-05-22-deep-code-security-review.md`\n    Finding: #25\n\n    ## Summary\n\n    CuPy modules are omitted from coverage, and GPU CI is allowed to fail.\n\n    ## Impact\n\n    CUDA code can regress without affecting quality gates.\n\n    ## Evidence\n\n    - `pyproject.toml:100`\n- `pyproject.toml:102`\n- `.gitlab-ci.yml:55`\n\n    ## Acceptance\n\n    - [ ] Keep CPU coverage separate if needed.\n- [ ] Add GPU coverage with its own threshold and reporting path.\n\n    ## Notes\n\n    This issue was filed from a read-only review. Confirm behavior with a focused failing test before implementation where practical.",
